<div id="content_header" class="clearfix">

  <% if flash[:notice] %>
    <div class="flash ui-widget">
      <div class="ui-state-highlight ui-corner-all">
        <%= flash[:notice] %>          
      </div>
    </div>
  <% end %>

  <%= image_tag('headings/hd_great_your_events_been_submitted.gif', :class => "heading") %>

      <h3 class="heading">Great - your event's now in the queue for moderation and as soon as it's been approved and added to the calendar, you'll be notified. Here's what you can do in the meantime:</h3>
  
</div>

<div class"events">
  
  <div class="content_wrapper">

        
    <ul class="post_event_choices row">
    
      <li class="content_block">

      <h4><%= image_tag 'headings/hd_add_another_event.gif', :alt => "Add another event to the listings" %></h4>

    <p>
      Have you got another event you could add to the calendar?    
    </p>
    
    <p>
      You can submit any event you think is suitable. You don't have to be running it yourself. 
    </p>
    
    <p><%= link_to "Add another event  &raquo;", current_events_path+"#new_event" %></p>

      </li>
    
      <li class="content_block">
    
      <h4><%= image_tag('headings/hd_promote_your_event.gif', :alt => "See our resources section") %></h4>

    <p>
      If you're running an event, it's usually essential to promote it well.
    </p>

    <p>
      We've got lots of tips and tricks to help make your event really successful.
    </p>
    
    <p><%= link_to "Promote your event &raquo;", "/promote-your-event" %></p>


      </li>

      <li class="content_block">
    
      <h4><%= image_tag('headings/hd_meet_other_organisers.gif', :alt => "Join our network on Ning") %></h4>

    <p>Join our social network to meet fellow event organisers.</p>
    
    <p>You can also share your views with us, and help to develop a culture of learning for all adults.</p>

    <p><%= link_to "Join our network on Ning", "http://thelearningrevolution.ning.com/" %></p>
    </li>

    
    </ul>
  
</div>

</div>
